source.name: Final Critical Habitat for the California Tiger Salamander (Ambystoma californiense) - Central Population
source.description: Abstract: These data identify, in general, the areas where final critical habitat for California tiger salamander (Ambystoma californiense), Central population, occur.     Purpose: Critical habitat are areas considered essential for the conservation of a listed species. These areas provide notice to the public and land managers the importance of these areas to the conservation of this species. Special protections and/or restrictions are possible in areas where federal funding, permits, licenses, authorizations, or actions occur or are required.
